WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.180
18.

00:08.900 --> 00:15.320
Through desire a man, having separated himself, seeketh and intermedaleth with all wisdom.

00:16.700 --> 00:22.080
A fool hath no delight in understanding, but that his heart may discover itself.

00:23.260 --> 00:28.860
When the wicked cometh, then cometh also contempt, and with ignominy reproach.

00:28.860 --> 00:35.900
The words of a man's mouth are as deep waters, and the wellspring of wisdom as a flowing brook.

00:36.900 --> 00:41.600
It is not good to accept the person of the wicked to overthrow the righteous in judgment.

00:43.200 --> 00:48.200
A fool's lips enter into contention, and his mouth calleth for strokes.

00:49.700 --> 00:55.300
A fool's mouth is his destruction, and his lips are the snare of his soul.

00:56.540 --> 01:03.820
The words of a tale-bearer are as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.

01:04.680 --> 01:10.660
He also, that is slothful in his work, is brother to him that is a great waster.

01:11.140 --> 01:17.220
The name of the Lord is a strong tower, the righteous runneth into it, and is safe.

01:18.080 --> 01:24.460
The rich man's wealth is his strong city, and as in high wall in his own conceit.

01:24.460 --> 01:30.700
Before destruction the heart of a man is haughty, and before honor is humility.

01:31.960 --> 01:36.900
He that answereth a matter before he heareth it, it is folly and shame unto him.

01:37.520 --> 01:43.240
The spirit of a man will sustain his infirmity, but a wounded spirit who can bear?

01:44.640 --> 01:51.220
The heart of the prudent man geteth knowledge, and the ear of the wise seeketh knowledge.

01:51.220 --> 01:57.260
A man's gift maketh room for him, and bringeth him before great men.

01:58.340 --> 02:04.840
He that is first in his own cause seemeth just, but his neighbor cometh and searcheth him.

02:05.640 --> 02:10.880
The lot causeth contentions to cease, and parteth between the mighty.

02:11.700 --> 02:18.900
A brother offended is harder to be won than a strong city, and their contentions are like the bars of a castle.

02:20.860 --> 02:28.240
A man's belly shall be satisfied with the fruit of his mouth, and with the increase of his lips shall he be filled.

02:29.800 --> 02:36.200
Death and life are in the power of the tongue, and they that love it shall eat the fruit thereof.

02:36.780 --> 02:42.160
Whoso findeth a wife findeth a good thing, and obtaineth favor of the Lord.

02:42.800 --> 02:46.860
The poor useth in treaties, but the rich answereth roughly.

02:46.860 --> 02:54.700
A man that hath friends must show himself friendly, and there is a friend that sticketh closer than a brother.

